10 Section 2. Section 61-8-502, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "61-8-502. Pedestrians' right-of-way in crosswalk -- school children -- pedestrian-actuated
12 devices. (1) (a) Except as provided in subsection (1)(b), when traffic control signals are not in place or not in
13 operation, the operator of a vehicle shall yield the right-of-way, slowing down or stopping if necessary, to a
14 pedestrian crossing the roadway within a marked crosswalk or within an unmarked crosswalk at an intersection,
15 but a pedestrian may not suddenly leave a curb or other place of safety and walk or run into the path of a
16 vehicle that is so close that it is impossible for the operator to yield. This provision does not apply under the
17 conditions provided in 61-8-503(2).
18 (b) When a vehicle is stopped at a marked crosswalk or at an unmarked crosswalk at an
19 intersection, the operator of a vehicle may make a right-hand turn if the pedestrian is in the opposite half of the
20 roadway and is not in danger.
21 (2) When a vehicle is stopped at a marked crosswalk or at an unmarked crosswalk at an
22 intersection to permit a pedestrian to cross the roadway, the operator of any other vehicle approaching from the
23 rear may not overtake and pass the stopped vehicle.
24 (3) A person may not operate a vehicle through a column of school children crossing a roadway or
25 past a school crossing guard while the crossing guard is directing the movement of children across a roadway
26 and while the crossing guard is holding an official sign in the stop position.
